@chavdar metadata about the ingestion data e.g. source, schema, timestamp etc. is written to the metadata.txt file. It could be json text or simple text. User can add this in config file. 
Its a no op if these configurations are not set.

IMO, its a good feature to have in gobblin.

Use case 
1. User needs to add information about the source of data
2. User adds json text in the configuration file.
3. Gobblin writes the json in metadata.txt after job completion.

> Made NewestKSelectionPolicy non-generic since the type is not used anywhere

It was made generic as part of https://github.com/linkedin/gobblin/pull/926 so code like this is possible:

```
NewestKSelectionPolicy<FileSystemDatasetVersion> test = new NewestKSelectionPolicy<>(1, true);
Collection<FileSystemDatasetVersion> selectedVersions = test.listSelectedVersions(Lists.<FileSystemDatasetVersion> newArrayList());
```

This is no longer possible with the given changes, unless do you a cast. Why does it need to be removed?

What's the issue with the `gobblin-tunnel` tests? This PR seems to disable a lot of them, which I agree we should do. The whole `gobblin-tunnel` module can probably have its tests disabled. In fact, `gobblin-tunnel` should probably be moved to a separate repo on GitHub.
Not sure, there were assert failures and NPEs. I'm disabling them to unblock Hudson build. We can re-enable them after we know what's wrong with them.
